# (empty/disabled - function overrides not used)
#
# Path to custom script containing function overrides
# Allows replacing protocol-specific implementations without modifying core script
#
# Use case: Replace pf firewall with ipfw, nftables, or iptables
# Example: /usr/local/etc/vpn-switch/.env/my_overrides.sh
#
# The override script is sourced after vpn-switch.sh
# Functions defined there replace default implementations
#
# To disable: Leave empty, use blank line, or start line with # (comment)
# All three are treated as "unset" by build_env_args()
